ad, festive cinnamon + oat protein donuts ! I can’t lie, I’ve had a bloody good time making these recipes for @whey.for.living’s new educational hub.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
whilst I most definitely enjoy my donuts without whey in them too, I think one of the final part of letting go of the nutrition bullshit we get fed here is actually embracing stuff you fancy eating that you might have previously rejected when you were angry at diet culture.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Like protein shakes. The pendulum swings from feeling like you *need* to blindly drink them to be ‘fitness’ to then vowing to never let one pass your lips again - to then actually realising its cool to have them sometimes. You know, if ya fancy it.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Same with protein baking. You don’t need to put whey in all of your baked goods, but (with the right recipe that doesn’t taste like soil) it can be a nice little boost. Again, if ya fancy it.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
what you need:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
- 100g blended oats⁠⠀
- 2 scoops vanilla whey protein (50g)⁠⠀
- 1 tsp baking powder⁠⠀
- pinch of salt⁠⠀
- 1 medium egg⁠⠀
- 175ml maple syrup⁠⠀
- 200ml milk⁠⠀
- 1 tsp vanilla essence⁠⠀
- 1 tbsp cinnamon⁠⠀
- 200g cream cheese⁠⠀
- 1 tsp green food colouring⁠⠀
⁠⠀
*6 part donut mould⁠⠀
⁠⠀
what you do:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
- preheat oven to 200dc⁠⠀
- blend your oats⁠⠀
- pour into a bowl⁠⠀
- add protein, salt + baking powder⁠⠀
- in a large separate mixing bowl, add eggs, 75g of maple syrup, milk + vanilla⁠⠀
- mix well + slowly add flour mixture, mixing as you go⁠⠀
- spoon into donut moulds evenly + smooth off the tops⁠⠀
- place in oven for approx 12 mins⁠⠀
- in a mixing bowl, add cream cheese, remaining maple syrup (100g) + cinnamon⁠⠀
- lick the mixture⁠⠀
- add green food colouring to preferred shade⁠⠀
- once donuts are cooked, take out oven⁠⠀
- once cooled, decorate w/ icing + other delicious cute things⁠⠀
⁠⠀
@whey.for.living⁠⠀
⁠⠀
#AD #WHEYFORLIVING

I’ll be honest - naturally I’m not good at being ‘the leader’. The thought of being responsible of anyone else apart from myself gives me major anxiety. Even in school, I would HATE having anyone over for tea after school - 3 hours of me being responsible for activities lol nope absolutely not. I’d always go to theirs. Even now, I hate picking where to meet for dinner when I’m with my mates and I am never a forth coming organiser. I can’t remember the last time I even made big plans for my birthday outside of seeing my family lmao. I don’t really know why - but it’s comfortable.

Which is why it’s still pretty wild that the nobs community not only exists - but also I created it. Mad.

This year I ran a retreat, I ran events, I ran 49 live streams to over 9,000 people and strangely, despite my character it felt like the most natural thing ever. I love fucking love taking responsibility for nobs. Give me all of it. ⠀
⁠⠀
Beyond all of the things I’m grateful for when it comes to my nobs - this is a huge personal achievement thing for me which is a testament to the vibe and energy each of you in there has created. I didn’t ever think we’d build what we built but here we are. And I’m forever grateful for all of you who are in the group, who give support, who come to meet ups, who make whatsapp groups, who message each other, who support each other’s businesses - all of it. You’re all real ones. And I love ya. 💖 ⠀
⁠⠀
{Tb to getting drunk at nobs xmas brunch, shot by @joymumfs at @daisygreencollection}

ad, protein gingerbread bread ! ! ! my former self used to be terrified of anything that said ‘high protein’ for fear it’d make me BuLkY.⠀
⠀
my former self has also been through a period where I couldn’t eat a damn slice of cake or chocolate bar with it been ‘protein-ified’. Because otherwise it wasn’t healthy. Whatever that is.⠀
⠀
Now - I simply get my protein from my food and a 'top up' with a whey protein. (Sometimes in the form of baked foods like this.)⠀
⠀
@whey.for.living are doing a great job at busting protein myths and showing you how and why you should / can incorporate whey into your day. No bs.⠀
⠀
Because after all, protein is a macronutrient our bodies need in order to function well in our everyday lives. And protein supplements, like whey - are just a way of letting us get a little more into our days.⠀
⠀
Do you need to sprinkle it on your cereal every morning? Absolutely not.⠀
But is it fun to bake it in a gingerbread bread as a little protein snack? Most definitely yes.⠀
⠀
(Plus if you eat the whole loaf, you’ll be pretty close to your daily protein requirement.)⠀
⠀
what you need:⠀
⠀
- 150g self raising flour⠀
- 3 scoops vanilla whey protein (75g)⠀
- 1 tbsp ground ginger⠀
- 1 tbsp allspice⠀
- 1 pinch salt⠀
- 1 tsp baking powder⠀
- 70g raisins⠀
- 150g black treacle⠀
- 60g butter unsalted⠀
- 60g brown sugar⠀
- 2 eggs⠀
- 200ml milk⠀
- 75g icing sugar⠀
- 4 tsp boiling water⠀
- edible glitter⠀
⠀
*electric mixer⠀
*2lb loaf tin⠀ ⠀
what you do:⠀
⠀
- preheat oven to 180 dc⠀
- pour flour into large mixing bowl⠀
- add protein, ginger, allspice, salt, baking powder + raisins⠀
- melt your butter in a separate bowl⠀
- add treacle +  sugar⠀
- once smooth, add this mixture to flour mixture⠀
- once ‘doughy’, add egg + milk⠀
- using an electric mixer, blend together⠀
- once thick and smooth, pour into loaf tin⠀
- smooth off the top + put in oven⠀
- bake for approx 45 mins⠀
- poke a knife down the centre to check if it’s cooked through⠀
- if it comes out clean, leave to cool on the side⠀
- mix together icing sugar + boiling water to make paste⠀
- decorate top of the gingerbread bread⠀
- add glitter cus it’s bloody christmas⠀
⠀
@whey.for.living #AD #wheyforliving

ad, lump-free protein hot chocolate ! what a time to be alive. I remember the days when I would attempt to swallow down bitty protein shakes, crying into my plastic shaker like IS THIS what this fitness thing is gunna be like??!!⁠⠀
⁠⠀
The answer is no - it’s not now - but I felt like it had to be back then lol. I thought protein shakes were these magical drinks which you were supposed the drink after training otherwise your session didn’t count. Whereas now, I know protein is just a macronutrient my body needs to support my muscle growth AND recovery - which is important for everyone, not just people who hit the gym a few times a week.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
@whey.for.living have actually created an accessible hub for all things protein - breaking down myths + fads when it comes to this macronutrient - which talks about exactly this.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I still supplement with whey protein, but just not in the form of clumpy powdered shakes. Instead I like to get a little creative with mine, having it in yoghurt, bakes + currently my new fave, hot chocolates. (I’ve also mastered the art of getting it silky smooth. Because nobody has times for bits, lumps and clumps. Urgh.)⁠⠀
⁠⠀
what you need:⁠⠀
- 1 scoop chocolate whey protein (25g)⁠⠀
- 1-2 tbsp milk⁠⠀
- boiling water⁠⠀
- handful mini marshmallows⁠⠀
⁠⠀
*also a smallish sieve⁠⠀
⁠⠀
what you do:⁠⠀
- sieve your protein into a medium-large mug⁠⠀
- add 1-2 tbsp milk + mix well into a paste⁠⠀
- boil your kettle + slowly add your water to the mug⁠⠀
- furiously mix as you pour, the slower the pour the better⁠⠀
- top with mini marshmallows⁠⠀
- enjoy your lump-free protein hot choc !⁠⠀
⁠⠀
@whey.for.living⁠⠀
⁠⠀
#AD #wheyforliving

CONTRARY TO POPULAR BELIEF, #FITNESS ISN’T JUST BULKING AND CUTTING EVERY 6 MONTHS UNTIL YOU DIE.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Whilst certain goals might require a particular kind of energy intake and movement output - there is also SO MUCH TO BE SAID for playing the long game.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
And just, well - eating.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Being on a creepy little bulking/cutting hamster wheel is a really good way to always be ‘chasing’ something you don’t have. And will never actually ‘get’. Because when the bulk ends, the cut starts and when the cut ends, the bulk starts again and so on.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Terrifying. So I’m just here popping up on your feed to let you know that your body doesn’t have to be some sort of weird art project that’s always a working progress.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
It’s okay to just train to train.⁠⠀
It’s okay to just eat to eat.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
My ‘fitness goals’ for next year will be the same as they have been the past two.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Continuing to lift weights regularly.⁠⠀
Continuing to get stronger.⁠⠀
Continuing to treat my body with respect.⁠⠀
Continuing to exclusively fill my plate with only things I actually like.⁠⠀
And continuing to not be a dick to myself for eating a donut or three..⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Merry bloody new year.

I don’t even know what to say tbh. I’m sitting here with a cup of tea (after many proseccos) trying to write a caption to describe how much a fucking love this community. But nothing really does it justice.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I love what we’ve built so much I could cry lol.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
We spend so much time and energy trying to reach this ambiguous level of ’wellness’ through what’s on our plate and hours in the gym, that we forget that community is a fundamental human need.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
And my vision for nobs has always gone way beyond the workout guides and the cookbook.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I wanted to create a community and family is what we got. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
One massive, weird family spending across the world - of humans who respect and support each other's goals, who *genuinely* want to each other do well and just want to have a bloody laugh over some pizza.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
And get occasionally sloppy-drunk in public places. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
This ‘fitness’ stuff can be so damn serious sometimes. I hope to change that.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
My stomach hurts from laughing so much today.⁠⠀
Thank you nobs. You’re a bloody great bunch.⁠⠀

me every damn new year from like 2010 till 2015. It’s weird how the brain works isn’t it? For such a long period of my life I was pretty much addicted to trying diets/fads/detox teas/waist trainers which I knew did not work. Like a toxic ex lol.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
For every new diet, for every new fad I would find within the depths of a google search - there was something within me that felt like it *must* work if someone said it did. It was like the desire to want to lose weight and get a bloody six pack outweighed any form of logic.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I felt like eating ‘well’ needed to be hard, miserable and coated in fucking spirulina from holland and barret.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
And when I’d try a weird new restrictive diet - which naturally I couldn’t stick to - I’d blame myself. Like I was the failure. BECAUSE GOD FORBID ! ! ! it was the weird new restrictive diet.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Please don’t carry this mindset with you into this next year. Seriously. Drop it now.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
In addition to 12 week workout plans, the existing @nobsguides (both gym guide + home guide) come with a nutrition PDF which breaks down all the fundamentals of nutrition, busts a shit load of myths, eating for your goal (if you have one at all) and basically teaches you how to build a cool, chilled relationship w/ food. We dropped it a year ago now and it will always stand the test of time. So if you have it - read it. And if you don’t have it and it sounds like your vibe, buy it. [Linked in bio]⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Be less Paris and safe guard yo self from the bullshit for 2020 and watch you THRIVE wooooo.⁠
